article_metadata.description: At the annual luncheon of the Health Care Foundation of Greater Kansas City, Sebelius expressed pride in what the Affordable Care Act has accomplished. The nation has seen a historic drop in the number of people without health insurance, she said, while health care inflation has been running at the lowest rate in 50 years.
